article.headline: S. Dakota State 21, North Dakota 0
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Tyler Duffy ran for 127 yards and two touchdowns in South Dakota State's 21-0 victory over North Dakota on Saturday. The Jackrabbits (5-6) defense made six sacks and held the Fighting Sioux (3-8) to 185 yards of total offense. South Dakota State's Thomas O'Brien completed 19 of 38 for 235 yards. He also connected with Alex Beyer on a 2-point conversion in the first quarter. Peter Reifenrath kicked a pair of field goals in the first quarter to give the Jackrabbits the early 6-0 lead. North Dakota's Brent Goska threw 11 for 27 for 90 yards. He was sacked twice and intercepted twice. Marcus Hendrickson was sacked the other four times and threw for just 6 yards.
